  "response": "Mint.com, the popular personal finance management service, was founded by **Aaron Patzer** in 2006. Aaron Patzer was the CEO and led the design and development of the platform. He conceptualized Mint.com as a way to help users easily manage their finances by aggregating their financial accounts into one place, providing budgeting tools, and offering insights into spending habits.\n\nMint.com was designed to be user-friendly and visually appealing, which contributed to its rapid success. The company was acquired by **Intuit** in 2009 for $170 million, and it remains a widely used financial tool today.",
